description:
Struggled a bit with pixels this week. I was using busy, colored images and was unable to set a threshold in order to get something that was radically different. For this sketch, I chose an image of scattered black dots on a white base, and then created ellipses and lines, sometimes at the same position, and sometimes offset by a certain amount. 

What was really interesting for me was the texture- the almost sharpie like feel in the first one versus the thick, acrylic layered look for the second. This was done by putting the stroke color in a for loop, and incrementing the r, g, b component each time the program would loop through. By adjusting the values and the stroke weights very different effects can be achieved. 

  for (var n = 0; n < 10; n++) {
          stroke(180 + 2 * n, 4 + (4 * n), 10);}

